if I could turn back time,

277
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:28,520
I wouldn't have denied
my feelings like I did.

278
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:33,200
I think we both should accept the truth.

279
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:37,200
No matter if it's good or bad,

280
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,560
we should still face it.

281
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:46,160
Well, how'd your trip go, Boss?

282
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:49,360
It made me more sure about things.

283
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,960
With the problem between me and Prao,

284
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:55,200
I'll make sure to solve it carefully,

285
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:58,960
so when the time comes,
and I have to decide,

286
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,440
I won't regret it.

287
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,760
You can stay here
and take care of Mr. Thee today.

288
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,920
I'll handle your work
for you at the office.

289
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:12,920
Thank you, Boss.

290
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,440
Boss,

291
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,920
I believe a good man like you

292
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,000
will surely be met with good things.

293
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:22,920
Good luck!

294
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,560
See you later.

295
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,720
What's wrong, Usa?

296
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:47,480
Mr. Thee was in an accident.

297
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:50,280
"THEE" BUSINESSMAN INJURED IN ACCIDENT
AFTER TRYING TO SAVE "KONGKWAN"

298
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,640
That's Kongkwan and Mook!

299
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:53,560
Wait!

300
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,800
Where are you going?

301
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,160
I'm going to see Mook.

302
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,920
I want to see how Kongkwan's doing.

303
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,320
Hold on!

304
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,920
Calm down, Kuk.

305
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,640
It says that the mom
and the daughter are safe.

306
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:07,480
Visiting Mook isn't what
we have to do right now.

307
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,480
Kongkwan!

308
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:32,400
How'd you get here, honey?

309
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:35,200
I took her.

310
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:39,400
I was the one who told Khim
to give me a ride here.

311
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:41,360
I wanted to cook him something too,

312
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:44,160
but I saw that you're busy,
so I didn't tell you.

313
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:47,600
And Kongkwan was begging
to visit Mr. Thee.

314
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,360
Is that true?

315
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,680
Mommy, come take a look!

316
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:04,480
Thee drew me.

317
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,000
Really? Let me see.

318
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:09,280
Can Mommy see?

319
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:12,040
Aw, how cute!

320
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:14,160
How is it? I'm good at drawing, right?

321
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,160
Here, look.

322
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,760
As pretty as in real life, right?

323
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:19,520
- You have to hold your hand up.
- My hand?

324
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:21,960
- Okay.
- There.

325
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,560
I think you're prettier in real life.

326
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:28,200
That's my daughter, alright.

327
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,200
What should we draw next?

328
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:32,600
Let me draw you next.

329
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:35,280
Sure. Here's your pencil.

330
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:40,920
His head's so big!

331
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:47,480
Hey.

332
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:05,080
Mr. Thee.

333
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:14,800
Done!

334
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:20,680
That's… how I look?!

335
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:22,440
- And what's that?
- A hat.

336
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:25,840
- Really?
- I have eyelashes too?

337
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:27,040
Mook.

338
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,120
Daddy!

339
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,280
Careful, honey.

340
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,880
What's up?

341
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,800
What are you doing here, Kongkwan?

342
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,960
I'm here to visit Thee.

343
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:43,920
Thee?

344
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:46,760
He's a friend of mine.

345
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,600
What's this about, Mook?

346
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,880
How come she's here with Mr. Thee,

347
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,800
and why do they seem so close?

348
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:09,560
Are you using our daughter?

349
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,280
Have some respect, Kuk.

350
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:15,840
I would never do such a thing.

351
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:19,000
She just wanted
to thank him for saving her.

352
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,160
Like I'd believe that.

353
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:26,400
Anyone can tell
you're trying to play house with them.

354
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,480
I really don't understand.

355
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,800
What else do you want?

356
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:34,480
Why are you using
our daughter to woo a guy?

357
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:36,360
You already won the deal,

358
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:39,360
but you weren't satisfied,
so now you want Mr. Thee too?

359
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:45,920
If I'm going to start
a new life with someone,

360
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:48,120
I reassure you,

361
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:51,440
I won't make the wrong decision again.

362
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:54,520
Sure.

363
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,440
We'll see about that.

364
00:32:57,400 --> 00:33:00,560
This path that you're choosing,
how good will it really be?

365
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,200
You should be taking care of Kongkwan,

366
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:05,000
yet you can't even do it right!

367
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:10,240
If something happens to her,
you're the one responsible.

368
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:36,160
I'm relieved to see

369
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:38,040
that you aren't badly hurt.

370
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,160
When I saw the news,

371
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:42,480
I was so worried about you, Mr. Thee.

372
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:51,160
Come to think of it,
ever since you met Mook,

373
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:54,280
I see you've had all kinds of trouble.

374
00:33:55,360 --> 00:33:59,880
I think you might want
to stay away from her sometimes.

375
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,120
Ms. Usa,

376
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:06,640
I don't think I can stay away
from someone I love.

377
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:11,719
I really don't know

378
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:16,239
what good you see in Mook
that makes you love her so much.

379
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:20,120
She's a single mom who got divorced,

380
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,320
and she isn't rich either.

381
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:24,679
She doesn't deserve you at all.

382
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:28,880
I never dated anyone
for their social status.

383
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:31,679
Let me be clear with you,

384
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:34,760
so you don't have to keep insulting her.

385
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:37,800
I love Mook.

386
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:40,480
I love everything about her.

387
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:45,480
- I think--
- Usa, let's go home.

388
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:49,960
Get well soon, Mr. Thee.

389
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,159
If you'll excuse me.

390
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,920
I don't care if you want to date Mook,

391
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:06,560
but don't drag my daughter into this.

392
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,360
I don't like it.

393
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,560
Kongkwan's asleep already?

394
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:39,880
Yes, Mom.

395
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:49,280
Is something wrong, Mook?

396
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:52,440
You've been quiet
since we got back from the hospital.

397
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,640
Did you and Kuk fight again?

398
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:01,320
Mom,

399
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,080
is it so wrong

400
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,760
if I choose what feels good
over what's right?

401
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:14,040
I don't know how to answer that.

402
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,920
Some people

403
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:20,720
choose what's right, yet they're unhappy,

404
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:23,000
and they have to put up
with it until they die.

405
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:29,160
Some people choose
what feels good over what's right,

406
00:36:29,240 --> 00:36:33,080
and still, there's no guarantee
they'll be happy until they die.

407
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,240
So,

408
00:36:37,520 --> 00:36:39,480
what should we choose, Mom?

409
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:44,080
You choose to do what makes you happy
without causing trouble for others,

410
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:48,760
and you must be sure
that it won't make others unhappy.

411
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:04,400
Being an adult sure is hard, Mom.

412
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:10,200
You like Mr. Thee, don't you?

413
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:22,080
Is it that obvious?

414
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,560
It's not hard to tell at all.

415
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:28,720
Mom.

416
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:34,080
So… would you mind

417
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:39,440
if I gave dating Mr. Thee a shot?

418
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,600
You're all grown up now.

419
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:43,720
You can make your own decisions.

420
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:46,920
From what I've seen,

421
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:49,240
Mr. Thee is a good man,

422
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:53,520
but time will tell, and we must let it.

423
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:27,360
What'd you talk to Mook about?

424
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,440
I was just reminding her
to behave herself,

425
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:34,120
since she's a mother.

426
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,520
And that Mr. Thee too.

427
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:39,720
I don't know why he's so in love with her.

428
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:40,840
Warning him's no use.

429
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:45,120
Since they started dating,
all they had is trouble.

430
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:51,680
I've never met anyone
as shameless as Mook.

431
00:38:52,320 --> 00:38:55,280
A single mom who's in the news
with a different guy every day.

432
00:38:56,440 --> 00:39:00,520
I feel so bad for your daughter
for having a mom like her.

433
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:10,200
I'll wait and see just how long
Mook and Mr. Thee will last.

434
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:13,600
A guy like Mr. Thee,
he's just having fun at most.

435
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:18,480
Your ex-wife, though,
is probably aiming for more.

436
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:50,040
{\an8}- Ploy didn't come into work?
- Yes.

437
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:52,320
She hasn't for a couple of days now.

438
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:54,880
I heard she's hospitalized too.

439
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:57,000
Hospitalized?

440
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,440
Do you know why?

441
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:01,560
No, she didn't specify.

442
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,280
Thank you.

443
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:12,280
ACCOUNTING

444
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:23,120
Khim, did you hear
about Ploy being in the hospital?

445
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:26,320
What?

446
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:38,160
You two are dealing
with such a horrible situation,

447
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:43,120
yet I never got to help
because I was so deep in my own mess.

448
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:47,040
It's all my fault.

449
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:49,120
At first, I was scared.

450
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:51,080
I couldn't admit the truth.

451
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:53,720
I thought things would die down,

452
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:59,400
but I never thought
Top could be such a monster.

453
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,440
Mook,

454
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:04,360
what should we do?

455
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:06,280
I feel bad for Ploy.

456
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:12,680
What about you? What will you do?

457
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:16,440
Just when your career's going well…

458
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:21,960
I don't care.

459
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:28,000
What I need to do right now
is drag Top to jail.

460
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:32,920
But If I expose him now,

461
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:36,360
Ploy will go down just as hard.

462
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:39,840
But we can't leave it like this.

463
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:42,840
We have to tell Ploy.

464
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:55,880
Ploy…

465
00:41:56,640 --> 00:42:00,080
Ploy will definitely hate me
if she hears the truth.

466
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,800
We're friends, you know.

467
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:08,480
I'm sure she'll understand.

468
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:51,440
If you'd behaved yourself,

469
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,280
you wouldn't have had to get hurt.

470
00:42:57,160 --> 00:42:58,600
I hope you learned

471
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,800
how you should behave from now on.

472
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:13,360
Hello?

473
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:16,800
I'm just heading out now.

474
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:19,360
See ya.

475
00:43:56,720 --> 00:44:01,240
MOOK

476
00:44:16,440 --> 00:44:18,720
Hello? What's up, Mook?

477
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:21,680
Ploy, we need to talk.

478
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:22,960
Where are you right now?

479
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:26,320
I'm in my room.

480
00:44:27,680 --> 00:44:29,240
Is there something urgent?

481
00:44:31,280 --> 00:44:33,160
<i>Now's not really a good time.</i>

482
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:35,520
<i>I'll let you know later, okay?</i>

483
00:44:37,400 --> 00:44:39,200
I want to see you too.

484
00:44:41,880 --> 00:44:43,160
<i>Talk to you later, Mook.</i>

485
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:46,280
Ploy! Ploy, Wait! Ploy!

486
00:44:58,080 --> 00:45:01,520
I won't let you two face
something so horrible again.

487
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:05,000
We'll get through this together.

488
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:12,360
It's okay.

489
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:27,600
<i>Ma, I'm filing for custody of Kongkwan.</i>

490
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:30,400
Why? What happened?

491
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:31,760
What did Mook do to her?

492
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:36,280
Well, yesterday, I visited Mr. Thee,

493
00:45:36,360 --> 00:45:38,160
and she took her to see him.

494
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:41,040
Kongkwan seemed so close to him, Ma.

495
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:45,680
That Mook is such a schemer.

496
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:48,960
She's planning to woo a rich guy
by using her daughter.

497
00:45:50,760 --> 00:45:54,440
I feel bad for my daughter, Ma,
so I want to take care of her myself.

498
00:45:56,960 --> 00:45:58,120
That's good.

499
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:02,320
She'll be devastated
to lose custody of her daughter to you.

500
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:04,680
No way!

501
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:06,720
You'll only fall right into her trap.

502
00:46:07,240 --> 00:46:08,800
Without her daughter around,

503
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:11,240
she'll win Mr. Thee over more easily.

504
00:46:12,960 --> 00:46:16,160
You're right. That's a good point, Usa.

505
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:17,720
Why should we take care of Kongkwan

506
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:20,640
and let Mook happily
roam free with her guy?

507
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:26,320
What should we do, then, Ma?

508
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:30,040
I can't stand seeing her happy
with another guy!

509
00:46:30,800 --> 00:46:32,680
Do you still have feelings for her?

510
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:38,080
That's not it, Usa.

511
00:46:39,240 --> 00:46:41,600
I just don't want her
to succeed in any way.

512
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:46,280
She already won the deal,
and now she's winning Mr. Thee over?

513
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:50,240
I won't let him take my place
and be Kongkwan's father.

514
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,320
Then don't let him!

515
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:04,800
WIH INTERNATIONAL HOSPITAL

516
00:47:38,240 --> 00:47:41,040
I'm here. I just had
to take care of something.

517
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,920
Please hurry. I miss you.

518
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:45,400
Okay.

519
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:06,160
Sorry.

520
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:33,480
Don't look at him that way.

521
00:48:34,200 --> 00:48:35,920
If Mr. Pitak didn't tell me,

522
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:38,080
I wouldn't have known
you're in a hospital.

523
00:48:41,560 --> 00:48:45,560
I wasn't hurt too badly,
so I didn't want you to worry.

524
00:48:46,520 --> 00:48:50,040
You're hospitalized,
yet you're saying it's not that bad?

525
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:53,160
You've changed a lot.

526
00:48:55,880 --> 00:48:58,320
What do you think you're doing?

527
00:48:58,960 --> 00:49:01,080
What if you get seriously hurt?

528
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:02,440
What about your company?

529
00:49:02,520 --> 00:49:05,800
So many people
would suffer because of you.

530
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:07,320
Not to mention our partners.

531
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:12,560
I'm well aware of what I'm doing.

532
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:15,200
You don't have to worry, Mom.

533
00:49:16,080 --> 00:49:19,560
I won't let our partners and employees
suffer because of me.

534
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:25,240
If that's true, why'd you do it?

535
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:29,720
You should know
what you're supposed to do.

536
00:49:30,360 --> 00:49:32,520
You can't get distracted like this.

537
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:34,840
And about Veluree too.

538
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:36,200
You--

539
00:49:42,040 --> 00:49:43,480
Please take this before your meal.

540
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:58,120
Perhaps I've been too kind to you.

541
00:49:59,680 --> 00:50:03,520
I'd better deal with everything
and whip it into shape.

542
00:50:05,160 --> 00:50:06,480
I hope you haven't forgotten

543
00:50:06,560 --> 00:50:10,120
the important job
you're supposed to be doing.

544
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:12,960
Take your pill.

545
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:46,320
{\an8}MOOK

546
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:01,960
Meet me at the print shop, Whan.

547
00:51:02,040 --> 00:51:04,440
Don't forget the laptop,
so I can edit it here.

548
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:06,760
Okay. See ya.

549
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:18,640
Mr. Thee, there's a problem with my work.

550
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:21,360
I just need to go edit it,
then I'll be right back.

551
00:51:23,360 --> 00:51:24,200
Okay.

552
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:32,880
I've finalized the artwork, Boss.

553
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:35,920
We should be able
to produce everything on time.

554
00:51:38,200 --> 00:51:39,240
Thank you for always

555
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:41,480
helping me solve the problems, Mook.

556
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:45,320
What are you working on, by the way?

557
00:51:45,400 --> 00:51:47,320
Why are there documents
all over your desk?

558
00:51:48,280 --> 00:51:50,400
I'm going over our financial summary.

559
00:51:52,520 --> 00:51:55,000
Although we've signed
the contract with The One,

560
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:58,840
I still need to get
a better handle on our cash flow.

561
00:51:59,440 --> 00:52:00,640
It's been a bit tight.

562
00:52:02,240 --> 00:52:04,360
Can I help you in any way?

563
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:06,000
Please just don't.

564
00:52:08,040 --> 00:52:10,760
This is for me and Mr. Suetrong to handle.

565
00:52:11,840 --> 00:52:14,680
I'm already really grateful
that you're handling

566
00:52:14,760 --> 00:52:16,400
almost everything for our company.

567
00:52:21,200 --> 00:52:22,120
Wanna grab dinner?

568
00:52:24,160 --> 00:52:26,560
If you'll excuse me,

569
00:52:27,080 --> 00:52:28,800
it's just…

570
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:30,240
You have a date with a sick guy.

571
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:33,280
Boss, don't make fun of me!

572
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:35,720
I'm going to visit Mr. Thee.

573
00:52:36,560 --> 00:52:38,560
See you later. Bye. You've got it, Boss.

574
00:53:18,520 --> 00:53:21,600
Just let me know when you want the fare.

575
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:35,640
{\an8}WIH INTERNATIONAL HOSPITAL

576
00:53:56,240 --> 00:53:57,200
Hey.

577
00:53:57,280 --> 00:53:58,280
Have a seat.

578
00:54:03,320 --> 00:54:04,440
Thank you.

579
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,160
Did you eat yet?

580
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:13,560
No. I came straight here
after I finished work.

581
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:16,160
Then let's eat together.

582
00:54:16,240 --> 00:54:18,520
I had Mr. Pitak buy us something simple

583
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:22,760
because I know you skip
your meals when you're busy.

584
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:26,040
Thank you.

585
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:30,440
Okay.

586
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:32,640
May I?

587
00:54:32,720 --> 00:54:33,680
Go ahead.

588
00:54:56,400 --> 00:54:57,560
Let me wipe your mouth.

589
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:01,640
It's okay. I've got it.

590
00:55:08,800 --> 00:55:11,200
So, what's the issue with work?

591
00:55:16,840 --> 00:55:19,200
The campaign's artwork
just needed an edit.

592
00:55:19,720 --> 00:55:21,640
I already took care of it, though.

593
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:28,160
I can leave tomorrow. I'll come help you.

594
00:55:29,560 --> 00:55:30,600
Really?

595
00:55:33,920 --> 00:55:37,120
But I wanted to ask you a favor.

596
00:55:40,280 --> 00:55:41,280
What is it?

597
00:55:44,280 --> 00:55:47,320
I want to eat your mom's cooking again.

598
00:55:49,560 --> 00:55:51,400
It's the best Thai food I've had

599
00:55:52,360 --> 00:55:54,440
since I got back in Thailand.

600
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,200
Would it be possible?

601
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:04,360
Please? I want to see Kongkwan too.

602
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:10,480
I'll go ask my mom.

603
00:56:11,120 --> 00:56:15,120
I don't know if she and Kongkwan
will say yes, though.

604
00:56:27,800 --> 00:56:29,080
You should have some too.

605
00:56:30,680 --> 00:56:32,200
Sure.

606
00:56:33,080 --> 00:56:36,080
Everything tastes good
when I'm eating with you.

607
00:56:41,520 --> 00:56:42,720
How is it?

608
00:56:58,520 --> 00:56:59,920
{\an8}How could you?!

609
00:57:01,120 --> 00:57:02,200
{\an8}I didn't start it.

610
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:04,320
{\an8}And actually,

611
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:08,640
{\an8}she slept with me
the night before we got married.

612
00:57:10,920 --> 00:57:12,160
{\an8}Khim.

613
00:57:12,240 --> 00:57:14,400
{\an8}- You want to say cheers that bad?
- Yes.

614
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:20,400
{\an8}You bitch!

615
00:58:27,760 --> 00:58:30,000
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

